text:
I have done some cooking classes and must say dis was C R I N G E.......nah jokin,it was actually adorable and she did her best ^^. It doesn't matter if your first creations are perfect, if it taste good you did great. 
Here's a easy recipe: 
600-630 grams of cake flour.
300-330 grams of caster sugar.
200 grams sunflower oil.
500 grams water.
10 (or as much you want) grams of cinnamon.
5 grams of clove
About 15-20 grams of baking powder.
250 grams of resins(the original recipe is a resin cake but nobody says you can't put chocolate or other stuff....or everything)
Just throw them all in a mixing bowl and mix till it looks like a cake batter ( don't worry,it will) then just flour and butter/oil a cake pan or a pan big enough, pour in your batter and let it to cook in a preheated oven of 170 celcious (or I guess 330 Fahrenheit)for about 40 mins.
During the end of cooking just use a toothpick to check it, poke the cake and if it comes out clean it's ready if not leave it for a little more. Enjoy.
